alert.note: Alert for Western Aleutians (Alaska) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: High Wind Warning issued November 18 at 12:35PM AKST until November 19 at 5:00AM AKST by NWS Anchorage
info.description: ...HIGH WIND WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 9 PM THIS EVENING TO 5 AM AKST SUNDAY... * WHAT...Southeast winds 55 to 65 mph with gusts up to 80 mph expected. * WHERE...Western Aleutians. * WHEN...From 9 PM this evening to 5 AM AKST Sunday. * IMPACTS...High winds may move loose debris, damage property, and cause power outages. Travel will be difficult. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...A strong low will push a front across the western Aleutians, bringing southerly winds and heavy rain. Winds will peak two separate times with the passage of this low. The first peak will occur tonight with the arrival of the front. Winds diminish to gale force on Sunday morning, before a second round of high winds on Sunday evening. Winds with the second round are not expected to exceed 75 mph at this time.
info.instruction: People are urged to secure loose objects that could be blown around or damaged by the wind. Prepare for the possibility of widespread power outages. Use caution if you must drive.
